# Cursor Project Rules

- Always inspect before editing.
- Always report planned file changes before implementing.
- Never change unrelated files.
- Never replace working logic without reason.
- Use Python 3.12.
- Use FastAPI, LangGraph, Pydantic v2, pytest, ruff, mypy.
- Store prompts in files, not giant inline strings.
- Use provider adapters for LM Studio.
- Keep file access bounded to workspace root.
- Never execute arbitrary shell commands from model output.
- All agent outputs must be structured and validated.
- Run lint, type checks, and tests after each milestone.
- Report exact validation results, not summaries.
- If blocked, stop and explain with concrete reasons.
